001package gust.backend.model;
002
003import com.google.protobuf.Message;
004
005import javax.annotation.Nonnull;
006import java.util.Map;
007
008
009/**
010 * Specifies a deserializer which is capable of converting generic Java {@link Map} objects (expected to have
011 * {@link String} keys) into arbitrary {@link Message} types.
012 *
013 * @param <Model> Model record type which this serializer is responsible for converting.
014 */
015public final class ObjectModelDeserializer<Model extends Message> implements ModelDeserializer<Map<String, ?>, Model> {
016  /**
017   * De-serialize a model instance from a generic Java map type, throwing exceptions verbosely if we are unable to
018   * correctly, verifiably, and properly load the record.
019   *
020   * @param input Input data or object from which to load the model instance.
021   * @return De-serialized and inflated model instance. Always a {@link Message}.
022   * @throws ModelInflateException If the model fails to load for any reason.
023   */
024  @Nonnull
025  @Override
026  public Model inflate(@Nonnull Map<String, ?> input) throws ModelInflateException {
027    return null;
028  }
029}
